Fix to work exactrly like bash
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.  Display a command prompt
  a.  input = readline("minishell> ");
2.  handle command input with history
  a.  add_history(input);
3.  Implement signal handling with minimal global variables.
  aa. should behave like in bash.
  a.  Handle ctrl-C
  b.  Handle ctrl-D
  c.  Handle ctrl-\
  ab.  In interactive mode:
  a.  ctrl-C displays a new prompt on a new line.
  b.  ctrl-D exits the shell.
  c.  ctrl-\ does nothing.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tokenize input -> Parse -> Execute
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
4.  Search and launch the right executable (based on the PATH variable or using a relative or an absolute path).
5.  Do Not interpret
  a.  unclosed quotes
  b.  special characters not required by the subject such as \ or ;
6.  Handle ’
  a.  should prevent the shell from interpreting the meta-characters in the quoted sequence.
7.  Handle "
  a.  should prevent the shell from interpreting the meta-characters in the quoted sequence except for $(dollar sign).
8.  Manage input/output redirection and piping.
  a.  >
  b.  <
  c.  >>
  d.  <<
  e.  |
9.  Handle environment variables
  a.  ($ followed by a sequence of characters) which should expand to their values.
10. Handle $?
  a.  should expand to the exit status of the most recently executed foreground pipeline.
11. Implement built-in commands
  a.  `echo`(with option -n)
  b.  `cd` (with only a relative or absolute path)
  c.  `pwd`
  d.  `export`
  e.  `unset`
  f.  `env`
  g.  `exit`
